    In [9]:
    # Linear function
n_samples = 10_000
x = np.linspace(-2, 2, n_samples)
y = x + 0.2 * np.random.randn(x.shape[0])
# x += 0.5 * np.random.randn(x.shape[0])
df = pd.DataFrame({
    'x': x,
    'y': y,

})

n_subset = 100

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,5))
pts1 = sns.scatterplot(ax=ax, data=df.sample(n=n_subset), x='x', y='y')
plt.tick_params(
    axis='both',          # changes apply to the x-axis
    which='both',      # both major and minor ticks are affected
    bottom=False,      # ticks along the bottom edge are off
    left=False,
    top=False,         # ticks along the top edge are off
    labelbottom=False,
    labelleft=False
)
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylabel('')
plt.tight_layout()
fig.savefig(
    FIG_PATH.joinpath('itm_linear_scatter.png'), 
    facecolor=None, transparent=True,
    dpi=100
)
plt.show()

    # linear function
n_samples = 1_000
seed = 123
rng = np.random.RandomState(seed=seed)

# nonlinear function
x = np.linspace(0.0, 2.5, n_samples)
y = 2 * np.sin(x) + 0.01 * rng.randn(n_samples)

df = pd.DataFrame({
    'x': x,
    'y': y,
})

n_subset = 100

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,5))

np.random.seed(123)
t = np.linspace(-2 * np.pi, 2 * np.pi, n_samples)
x = np.cos(t)  # + noise_x * rng_x.randn(num_points, 1)
y = np.sin(t)

df = pd.DataFrame({

    'y': y,
})
